data.description: Mountain Retreat Estate in North Idaho on 40 acres square; nestled among the native North Idaho Timber is a custom built and finished home that is a must see. This property lends itself best to those who are looking for lots of room for Family and/or Guests. Boasting 2 Large En-Suite Living areas and multiple guest bedrooms this could well work as a multi-generation or multi-family living environment. 2 Shops with power and water nearby, provide enough room for projects and/or storage for both the pro and hobbyist. A 3 GPM well fills the 5K gallon cistern – water is the new Gold and there is plenty of it. The custom-built Green House and Potting Shed; Chicken Coops and Wildlife Feeding/Viewing station always keep you busy. Private Road access keeps your living and lifestyle secure and private. Private Roads and Trails throughout the property allowing for exploration and access of all 40 acres. Discover marketable Timber and valuations via timber cruise provided by a local logging agency. Honeywell propane generator powers the main part of the house in case of outages. Outdoor recreation and activities abound on the mountain. Hiking, 4-wheeling, hunting, wildlife watching and winter sports like snowshoeing, XC skiing and even snowmobiling are right at your fingertips. Just down the hill is the Lake Cocolalla Sportsman’s access offering you the opportunity for fun on the water year-round including wakeboarding and surfing, kayaking, SUP’s and more. Fishing on Lake Cocolalla is unmatched year-round – yes catch the Ice Fishing craze. Whether looking for a self-sustaining property or a private estate getaway, the peace, tranquility and privacy you will find on Oak Terrace is unmatched. Proximity to regional destination highlights like Silverwood Theme Park and Schweitzer Mountain Ski Resort – both 30 minutes away. See the Feature Sheet for more property details.
